bel Allende|Isabel '''Allende''']] (born 1942), [[Bestseller|best selling]] novelist.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[D\u00e1maso Alonso|D\u00e1maso '''Alonso''']] (1898\u20131990), poet, [[Cervantes Prize]] Laureate (1978).\n*[[File:Flag of Peru.svg|25px|Peru]] [[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Arguedas|Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda '''Arguedas''']] (1911\u20131969), novelist.\n*[[File:Flag of the Philippines.svg|25px|Philippines]] [[Cecilio Ap\u00f3stol|Cecilio '''Ap\u00f3stol''']] (1877&ndash;1938), poet.\n*[[File:Flag of Argentina.svg|25px|Argentina]] [[Roberto Arlt|Roberto '''Arlt''']] (1900\u20131942), short-story writer, novelist, and playwright.\n*[[File:Flag of Guatemala.svg|25px|Guatemala]] [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Asturias|Miguel \u00c1ngel '''Asturias''']] (1899\u20131974), [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel Prize]] Laureate (1967).\n*[[File:Flag of Equatorial Guinea.svg|25px|Equatorial Guinea]] [[Juan Tom\u00e1s \u00c1vila Laurel|Juan Tom\u00e1s '''\u00c1vila Laurel''']] (born 1966), writer and dissident.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Francisco Ayala (novelist)|Francisco '''Ayala''']] (1906&ndash;2009), novelist, [[Cervantes Prize]] Laureate (1991).\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Jos\u00e9 Mart\u00ednez Ruiz|'''Azor\u00edn''' (Jos\u00e9 Mart\u00ednez Ruiz)]] (1863\u20131967), journalist, poet, novelist and essayist.\n*[[File:Flag of the Philippines.svg|25px|Philippines]] [[Jes\u00fas Balmori|Jes\u00fas '''Balmori''']] (1887&ndash;1948), journalist, poet, novelist.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[P\u00edo Baroja|P\u00edo '''Baroja''']] (1872\u20131956), novelist.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Gustavo Adolfo B\u00e9cquer|Gustavo Adolfo '''B\u00e9cquer''']] (1836\u20131870), [[Romanticism|romantic]] poet and tale writer.\n*[[File:Flag of Venezuela.svg|25px|Venezuela]] [[File:Flag of Chile.svg|25px|Chile]] [[Andr\u00e9s Bello|Andr\u00e9s '''Bello''']] (1781\u20131865), humanist, poet, lawmaker, philosopher and educator.\n*[[File