x|Mexico]] [[Gabriel Zaid|Gabriel '''Zaid''']] (born 1934), poet and essayist.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Mar\u00eda de Zayas y Sotomayor|Mar\u00eda de '''Zayas y Sotomayor''']] (1590\u20131660), novelist.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Jos\u00e9 Zorrilla y Moral|Jos\u00e9 '''Zorrilla y Moral''']] (1817\u20131893), poet and dramatist, author of ''[[Don Juan Tenorio]]'' (1844).\n\n== Film directors ==\n{{see also|Category:Spanish-language film directors}}\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Pedro Almod\u00f3var|Pedro '''Almod\u00f3var''']] (born 1949)\n*[[File:Flag of Chile.svg|20px|Chile]] [[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Alejandro Amen\u00e1bar|Alejandro '''Amen\u00e1bar''']] (born 1972)\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|20px|Mexico]] [[Alfonso Arau|Alfonso '''Arau''']] (born 1932)\n*[[File:Flag of Argentina.svg|20px|Argentina]] [[Adolfo Aristarain|Adolfo '''Aristarain''']] (born 1943)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Ic\u00edar Bolla\u00edn|Ic\u00edar '''Bolla\u00edn''']] (born 1967)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|20px|Mexico]] [[Luis Bu\u00f1uel|Luis '''Bu\u00f1uel''']] (1900\u20131983)\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|20px|Mexico]] [[Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n|Alfonso '''Cuar\u00f3n''']] (born 1961)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Cuerda|Jos\u00e9 Luis '''Cuerda''']] (born 1947)\n*[[File:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|20px|Puerto Rico]] [[Nelson Denis|Nelson '''Denis''']] (born 1954)\n*[[File:Flag of Chile.svg|20px|Chile]] [[Juan Downey|Juan '''Downey''']] (born 1947)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[V\u00edctor Erice|V\u00edctor '''Erice''']] (born 1940)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Garci|Jos\u00e9 Luis '''Garci''']] (born 1944)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Luis Garc\u00eda Berlanga|Luis '''Garc\u00eda Berlanga''']] (born 1921)\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|20px|Mexico]] [[Alejandro Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu|Alejandro '''Gonz\u00e1lez I\u00f1\u00e1rritu''']] (born 1963)\n*[[File:Flag of Chile.svg|20px|Chile]] [[Alexandro Jodorowsky|Alexandro '''Jodorowsky''']] (born 1929)\n*[[File:Flag of Argentina.svg|20px|Argentina]] [[Le\u00f3n Klimovsky|Le\u00f3n '''Klimovsky''']] (1906\u20131996)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Bigas Luna|Bigas '''Luna''']] (1946\u20132013)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Julio M\u00e9dem|Julio '''M\u00e9dem''']] (born 1958)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Paul Naschy|Paul '''Naschy''']] (born 1934)\n*[[File:Flag of Venezuela.svg|20px|Venezuela]] [[Franco de Pe\u00f1a|Franco de '''Pe\u00f1a''']] (born 1966)\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|20px|Mexico]] [[Arturo Ripstein|Arturo '''Ripstein''']] (born 1943)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Carlos Saura|Carlos '''Saura''']] (born 1932)\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|20px|Mexico]] [[Guillermo del Toro|Guillermo del '''Toro''']] (born 1964)\n\n== Journalists ==\n*[[File:Flag of Argentina.svg|20px|Argentina]] [[Enrique Gratas|Enrique '''Gratas''']], [[Television news|television]] [[Electronic journalism|journalist]].\n*[[File:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|20px|Puerto Rico]] [[Jorge L. Ramos|Jorge L. '''Ramos''']] (born 1950), television journalist; three-time [[Emmy Award]] winner.\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|20px|Mexico]] [[Jacobo Zabludovsky|Jacobo '''Zabludovsky''']] (born 1928), television journalist.\n\n== Linguists ==\n*[[File:Flag of Venezuela.svg|20px|Venezuela]] [[File:Flag of Chile.svg|20px|Chile]] [[Andr\u00e9s Bello|Andr\u00e9s '''Bello''']] (1781\u20131865), [[Philology|philologist]].\n*[[File:Flag of Colombia.svg|20px|Colombia]] [[Miguel Antonio Caro|Miguel Antonio '''Caro''']] (1843\u20131909), [[Linguistics|linguist]].\n*[[File:Flag of Colombia.svg|20px|Colombia]] [[Rufino Jos\u00e9 Cuervo|Rufino Jos\u00e9 '''Cuervo''']] (1844\u20131911), philologist and linguist.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Mar\u00eda Moliner|Mar\u00eda '''Moliner''']] (1900\u20131981), [[lexicographer]].\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|20px|Spain]] [[Antonio de Nebrija|Antonio de '''Nebrija''']] (1441\u20131522), scholar, published the first grammar of the [[Spanish language]] (''[[Gram\u00e1tica Castellana]]'', 1492), which was the first grammar produced of any [[Romance language]].\n\n== Singers and songwriters ==\n:''See also [[Spanish language rock and roll]] (by country).''\n*[[File:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|25px|Puerto Rico]] [[Lucecita Ben\u00edtez|Lucecita '''Benitez''']] (born 1940), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|25px|Puerto Rico]] [[Nydia Caro|Nydia '''Caro''']] (born 1955), singer.\n*[[File:Flag of the Philippines.svg|25px|Philippines]] [[Pilita Corrales|Pilita '''Corrales''']] (born 1939), singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Cuba.svg|25px|Cuba]] [[Celia Cruz|Celia '''Cruz''']] (1926\u20132003), [[Salsa music|salsa]] singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Cuba.svg|25px|Cuba]] [[Gloria Estefan|Gloria '''Estefan''']] (born 1957), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|25px|Puerto Rico]] [[Jos\u00e9 Feliciano|Jos\u00e9 '''Feliciano''']] (born 1945), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|25px|Puerto Rico]] [[Luis Fonsi|Luis '''Fonsi''']] (born 1978), singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|25px|Mexico]] [[Juan Gabriel|Juan '''Gabriel''']] (born 1950), ''[[ranchera]]'' and [[ballad]] singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Manolo Garc\u00eda|Manolo '''Garc\u00eda''']] (born 1955), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of France.svg|25px|France]] [[Carlos Gardel|Carlos '''Gardel''']] (1890\u20131935), [[Tango music|tango]] singer born in France, raised in Argentina.\n*[[File:Flag of the Dominican Republic.svg|25px|Dominican Republic]] [[Juan Luis Guerra|Juan Luis '''Guerra''']] (born 1957), [[Merengue music|merengue]]  and [[Bachata (music)|bachata]]  singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Julio Iglesias|Julio '''Iglesias''']] (born 1943), pop singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|25px|Mexico]] [[Pedro Infante|Pedro '''Infante''']] (1917\u20131957)\n*[[File:Flag of Chile.svg|25px|Chile]] [[V\u00edctor Jara|V\u00edctor '''Jara''']] (1932\u20131973), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|25px|Mexico]] [[Jos\u00e9 Alfredo Jim\u00e9nez|Jos\u00e9 Alfredo '''Jim\u00e9nez''']] (1926\u20131973), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Colombia.svg|25px|Colombia]] '''[[Juanes]]''' (born 1972), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|25px|Mexico]] [[Agust\u00edn Lara|Agust\u00edn '''Lara''']] (1900\u20131970), singer and songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Italy.svg|25px|Italy]] [[Laura Pausini|'''Laura''' Pausini]] (born 1974), singer and songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Cuba.svg|25px|Cuba]] [[Ernesto Lecuona|Ernesto '''Lecuona''']] (1896\u20131963), songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|25px|Puerto Rico]] '''[[Marc Anthony]]''' (born 1969), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Puerto Rico.svg|25px|Puerto Rico]] [[Ednita Nazario|Ednita '''Nazario''']] (born 1955)\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|25px|Mexico]] [[Jorge Negrete|Jorge '''Negrete''']] (1911\u20131953)\n*[[File:Flag of the United States.svg|25px|U.S.A.]] '''[[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]''' (born 1981), pop singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Mexico.svg|25px|Mexico]] [[Jos\u00e9 Alfredo Jim\u00e9nez|Jose Alfredo '''Jimenez''']] (1926\u20131973)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] '''[[Nino Bravo]]''' (1944\u20131973)\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] '''[[Raphael (singer)|Raphael]]''' (born 1943), pop singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Joaqu\u00edn Sabina|Joaqu\u00edn '''Sabina''']] (born 1949), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Alejandro Sanz|Alejandro '''Sanz''']] (born 1968), [[Pop music|pop]]/[[ballad]] singer.\n*[[File:Flag of the United States.svg|25px|U.S.A.]] '''[[Selena]]''' (1971\u20131995), pop singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Joan Manuel Serrat|Joan Manuel '''Serrat''']] (born 1943), singer-songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Colombia.svg|25px|Colombia]] '''[[Shakira]]''' (born 1977), [[Latin Pop]] singer and songwriter.\n*[[File:Flag of Spain.svg|25px|Spain]] [[Enrique Urquijo|Enrique '''Urquijo''']] (1960\u20131999), [[New wave music]] singer.\n*[[File:Flag of Argentina.svg|25px|Argentina]] [[Atahualpa Yupanqui|Atahualpa '''Yupanqui''']] (1908\u20131992), [[folk music]]ian.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of arabophones]]\n*[[List of people by nationality]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hispanophones}}\n[[Category:Lists of people by language]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language lists]]\n[[Category:Hispanidad]]\n", "name_user": "Doomwings13", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eE-H", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_hispanophones"}
{"title_page": "Medine Erkan", "text_new": "{{short description|Turkish women's football defender|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Medine Erkan\n| fullname    = \n| image       = MedineErkan 08.JPG\n| i\u00f6age_size  = \n| caption     = Medine Erkan in the [[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315 season]].\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1995|09|10}}\n| birth_place = [[Eski\u015fehir]], Turkey\n| currentclub = [[ALG Spor]]\n| clubnumber  = 8\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[Eski\u015fehirspor (women)|Eski\u015fehirspor]]\n| caps1  = 49\n| goals1 = 15\n| years2 = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs2 = [[Derince Belediyespor (women)|Derince Belediyespor]]\n| caps2  = 17\n| goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs3 = [[Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor]]\n| caps3  = 40\n| goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs4 = [[Kocaeli Bayan FK]]\n| caps4  = 28\n| goals4 = 13\n| years5 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[ALG Spor]]\n| caps5  = 10\n| goals5 = 1\n| totalcaps  = \n| totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2010\n| nationalteam1  = [[Turkey women's national under-15 football team|Turkey U-15]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2012\u20132014\n| nationalteam2  = [[Turkey women's national under-19 football team|Turkey U-19]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 26\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2016\u2013\n| nationalteam3  = [[Turkey women's national football team|Turkey]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 14\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| club-update         = January 5, 2020\n| nationalteam-update = November 11, 2016\n}}\n\n'''Medine Erkan''' (born September 10, 1995) is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] [[women's soccer|women's football]] [[Defender (association football)|defender]] currently playing in the Turkish Women's Third League for [[ALG Spor]] with jersey number 8. She plays for the [[Turkey women's national football team|Turkish women's national team]].<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\n==Career==\n===Club===\n[[File:MedineErkan 06.JPG|thumb|upright|left|Medine Erkan for [[Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor]] ([[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315 season]]).]]\n[[File:MedineErkan 02.JPG|thumb|upright|Medine Erkan playing for [[Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor]] in the [[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315 season]].]]\nMedine Erkan received her license on February 9, 2010 for her hometown club [[Eski\u015fehirspor (women)|Eski\u015fehirspor]], where she played four seasons in the Regional League, [[Turkish Women's Second Football League|Women's Second League]] and finally Women's First League.<ref name=\"2e\"/><ref name=\"as\"/> In the 2013\u201314 season, she transferred to [[Derince Belediyespor (women)|Derince Belediyespor]].<ref name=\"aa1\"/><ref name=\"s365\"/> After one season, Derince Belediyespor withdrew from the league, and Erkan moved to play with Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor in the [[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315 season]].<ref name=\"s26\"/>\n\nBy end September 2019, she transferred to [[ALG Spor]] in [[Gaziantep]].<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\n===International===\nMedine Erkan was admitted to the [[Turkey women's national under-15 football team|Turkey U-15]], and debuted in the [[Football at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics \u2013 Girls' tournament|2010 summer Youth Olympics]] held in [[Singapore]], and capped four time.<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\nOn September 26, 2012, Erkan played for the first time at the [[Turkey women's national under-19 football team|Turkey U-19]] appearing in the friendly match against Wales. She played in the [[2013 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship First qualifying round#Group 5|2013 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship First qualifying round \u2013 Group 5]], 2013 Kuban Spring Tournament,<ref name=\"f1\"/> [[2014 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification#Group 10|2014 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification \u2013 Group 10]],<ref name=\"2e\"/> 2014 Kuban Spring Tournament and [[2014 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification#Group 5|2014 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification \u2013 Group 5]] matches. She capped 32 times for the women's national U-19 team.<ref name=\"tff0\"/><ref name=\"as\"/><ref name=\"s26\"/><ref name=\"trt1\"/><ref name=\"ag1\"/><ref name=\"eo1\"/>\n\nErkan was admitted to the [[Turkey women's national football team|national team]] and played in three matches of the [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 qualifying Group 5]].<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played January 5, 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|National\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=5 |[[Eski\u015fehirspor (women)|Eski\u015fehirspor]]\n|2009\u201310\n|[[Women's football in Turkey#Women's Regional League|Regional League]]\n|10 ||0 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||2 ||0 ||12 ||0\n|-\n|2010\u201311\n|Regional League\n|10 ||1 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||0 ||0 ||10 ||1\n|-\n|2011\u201312\n|[[Turkish Women's Second Football League|Second League]]\n|11 ||8 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||0 ||0 ||11 ||8\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Turkish Women's First Football League|2012\u201313]]\n|[[Turkish Women's First Football League|First League]]\n|18 ||6 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||10 ||0 ||28 ||6\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!49 !!15 !! \u2013 !! \u2013 !!12 !!0 !!61 !!15\n|-\n|rowspan=2 |[[Derince Belediyespor (women)|Derince Belediyespor]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Turkish Women's First Football League|2013\u201314]]\n|First League\n|17 ||2 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||16 ||0 ||33 ||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!17 !!2 !! \u2013 !! \u2013 !!16 !!0 !!33 !!2\n|-\n|rowspan=4 |[[Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor]]\n|[[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315]]\n|First League\n|17 ||1 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||0 ||0 