urkish |accessdate=2014-12-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141211124534/http://www.atasehiraktuel.com/atasehir-belediyespor-bayan-futbol-takimi-maci-5-0-aldi.html |archivedate=2014-12-11 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"eo1\">{{cite news |url=http://ereglionder.com.tr/haber/kizlar-bosna39yi-devirdi/48196/ |newspaper=Ere\u011fli \u00d6nder |title=K\u0131zlar Bosna'y\u0131 devirdi |date=2013-04-09 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2014-12-11 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"s365\">{{cite news |url=http://www.spor365.com/Derincespor-calismalara-yogunlasti_15405.html |newspaper=Spor 365 |title=Derincespor \u00e7al\u0131\u015fmalara yo\u011funla\u015ft\u0131 |date=2014-04-09 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2014-12-11 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{UEFA player|250056494}}\n* {{FIFA|325129}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Erkan, Medine}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:ALG Spor players]]\n[[Category:Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor players]]\n[[Category:Derince Belediyespor women's players]]\n[[Category:Eski\u015fehirspor women's players]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics]]\n[[Category:Kocaeli Bayan FK players]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Eski\u015fehir]]\n[[Category:Turkey women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Turkish women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Women's association football defenders]]\n\n{{Turkey-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Turkish women's football defender|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Medine Erkan\n| fullname    = \n| image       = MedineErkan 08.JPG\n| i\u00f6age_size  = \n| caption     = Medine Erkan in the [[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315 season]].\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1995|09|10}}\n| birth_place = [[Eski\u015fehir]], Turkey\n| currentclub = [[ALG Spor]]\n| clubnumber  = 8\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[Eski\u015fehirspor (women)|Eski\u015fehirspor]]\n| caps1  = 49\n| goals1 = 15\n| years2 = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs2 = [[Derince Belediyespor (women)|Derince Belediyespor]]\n| caps2  = 17\n| goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs3 = [[Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor]]\n| caps3  = 40\n| goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs4 = [[Kocaeli Bayan FK]]\n| caps4  = 28\n| goals4 = 13\n| years5 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[ALG Spor]]\n| caps5  = 10\n| goals5 = 1\n| totalcaps  = \n| totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2010\n| nationalteam1  = [[Turkey women's national under-15 football team|Turkey U-15]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2012\u20132014\n| nationalteam2  = [[Turkey women's national under-19 football team|Turkey U-19]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 26\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2016\u2013\n| nationalteam3  = [[Turkey women's national football team|Turkey]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 14\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| club-update         = Januray 5, 2020\n| nationalteam-update = November 11, 2016\n}}\n\n'''Medine Erkan''' (born September 10, 1995) is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] [[women's soccer|women's football]] [[Defender (association football)|defender]] currently playing in the Turkish Women's Third League for [[ALG Spor]] with jersey number 8. She plays for the [[Turkey women's national football team|Turkish women's national team]].<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\n==Career==\n===Club===\n[[File:MedineErkan 06.JPG|thumb|upright|left|Medine Erkan for [[Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor]] ([[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315 season]]).]]\n[[File:MedineErkan 02.JPG|thumb|upright|Medine Erkan playing for [[Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor]] in the [[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315 season]].]]\nMedine Erkan received her license on February 9, 2010 for her hometown club [[Eski\u015fehirspor (women)|Eski\u015fehirspor]], where she played four seasons in the Regional League, [[Turkish Women's Second Football League|Women's Second League]] and finally Women's First League.<ref name=\"2e\"/><ref name=\"as\"/> In the 2013\u201314 season, she transferred to [[Derince Belediyespor (women)|Derince Belediyespor]].<ref name=\"aa1\"/><ref name=\"s365\"/> After one season, Derince Belediyespor withdrew from the league, and Erkan moved to play with Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor in the [[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315 season]].<ref name=\"s26\"/>\n\nBy end September 2019, she transferred to [[ALG Spor]] in [[Gaziantep]].<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\n===International===\nMedine Erkan was admitted to the [[Turkey women's national under-15 football team|Turkey U-15]], and debuted in the [[Football at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics \u2013 Girls' tournament|2010 summer Youth Olympics]] held in [[Singapore]], and capped four time.<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\nOn September 26, 2012, Erkan played for the first time at the [[Turkey women's national under-19 football team|Turkey U-19]] appearing in the friendly match against Wales. She played in the [[2013 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship First qualifying round#Group 5|2013 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship First qualifying round \u2013 Group 5]], 2013 Kuban Spring Tournament,<ref name=\"f1\"/> [[2014 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification#Group 10|2014 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification \u2013 Group 10]],<ref name=\"2e\"/> 2014 Kuban Spring Tournament and [[2014 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification#Group 5|2014 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification \u2013 Group 5]] matches. She capped 32 times for the women's national U-19 team.<ref name=\"tff0\"/><ref name=\"as\"/><ref name=\"s26\"/><ref name=\"trt1\"/><ref name=\"ag1\"/><ref name=\"eo1\"/>\n\nErkan was admitted to the [[Turkey women's national football team|national team]] and played in three matches of the [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 qualifying Group 5]].<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played January 5, 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|National\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=5 |[[Eski\u015fehirspor (women)|Eski\u015fehirspor]]\n|2009\u201310\n|[[Women's football in Turkey#Women's Regional League|Regional League]]\n|10 ||0 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||2 ||0 ||12 ||0\n|-\n|2010\u201311\n|Regional League\n|10 ||1 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||0 ||0 ||10 ||1\n|-\n|2011\u201312\n|[[Turkish Women's Second Football League|Second League]]\n|11 ||8 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||0 ||0 ||11 ||8\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Turkish Women's First Football League|2012\u201313]]\n|[[Turkish Women's First Football League|First League]]\n|18 ||6 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||10 ||0 ||28 ||6\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!49 !!15 !! \u2013 !! \u2013 !!12 !!0 !!61 !!15\n|-\n|rowspan=2 |[[Derince Belediyespor (women)|Derince Belediyespor]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Turkish Women's First Football League|2013\u201314]]\n|First League\n|17 ||2 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||16 ||0 ||33 ||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!17 !!2 !! \u2013 !! \u2013 !!16 !!0 !!33 !!2\n|-\n|rowspan=4 |[[Ata\u015fehir Belediyespor]]\n|[[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's First Football League|2014\u201315]]\n|First League\n|17 ||1 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||0 ||0 ||17 ||1\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Turkish Women's First Football League|2015\u201316]]\n|First League\n|17 ||0 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||3 ||0 ||20 ||0\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Turkish Women's First Football League|2016\u201317]]\n|First League\n|6 ||0 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||0 ||0 ||6 ||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!40 !!1 !! \u2013 !! \u2013 !!3 !!0 !!43 !!1\n|-\n|rowspan=3 |[[Kocaeli Bayan FK]]\n|2017\u201318\n|Third League\n|8 ||4 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||0 ||0 ||8 ||4\n|-\n|2018\u201319\n|Second League\n|20 ||9 || \u2013 || \u2013 ||5 ||0 ||25 ||9\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!28 !!13 !! \u2013 !! \u2013 